('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:mcq:adf8943e', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "What is the noun that goes with the verb ‘doler’ (to hurt)?", "options": ["el dolor", "el dolido", "el duelo", "el dolorido"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "el dolor = pain. ‘el duelo’ (duel/mourning) and ‘dolorido’ (sore, an adjective) are real but different words — classic look-alike traps."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:mcq:7510ab26', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "‘Mi abuelo se cayó’ means…", "options": ["My grandad fell over", "My grandad is going to fall over", "My grandad never falls over", "My grandad falls over often"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "se cayó is the preterite (past) of caerse. The traps change it to future, or add ‘never’/‘often’ that was never said."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:mcq:f497828d', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which is the best advice to relax?", "options": ["Hay que respirar profundamente", "Hay que respirar lo menos posible", "No se debe respirar durante el ejercicio", "Se debe dejar de respirar un momento"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Good advice: breathe deeply. The traps tell you to breathe as little as possible, not breathe while exercising, or stop breathing."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:tf:8ca2465b', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘doler’ works like ‘gustar’ — it agrees with the body part, not the person."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "Me duele la cabeza / me duelen los pies — the verb matches the body part."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:tf:178f0046', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘Estoy constipado’ means ‘I am constipated’."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "False friend! It means ‘I have a cold’."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:tf:eb9718c3', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘se debe’ is followed by an infinitive."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "se debe descansar / fumar / dormir — always an infinitive."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:tf:8e65815c', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘dejar de fumar’ means ‘to start smoking’."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "dejar de + infinitive = to STOP doing something — to stop smoking."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:tf:a64d29f0', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "For temporary feelings like ‘tired’ you use ‘estar’ (estoy cansado)."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "Temporary states use estar, not ser."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:tf:e5dd34ab', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘la garganta’ means ‘the stomach’."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": false, "explain": "la garganta = throat; el estómago = stomach."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:tf:fefe9cfe', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘acostarse’ is a reflexive verb, so ‘I go to bed’ is ‘me acuesto’."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "Reflexive: me acuesto, te acuestas, se acuesta."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice:tf:ad3d11ad', 'spanish', 'spanish:2-2-exercise-health-problems-and-advice', '2.2 Exercise, Health Problems and Advice', 'tf', 'tf', 1, '{"question": "‘Se debería evitar el estrés’ uses the conditional and suits Higher tier."}'::jsonb, '{"answer": true, "explain": "se debería = one should (conditional)."}'::jsonb),
